Young Amazons trained outside in the sun..thankful to be out of the dark covering of the Trainer's hut.  The scent of steam and charcoal could be smelled from the smith's barn..the clank of metal....and the sounds of horses flirting in the fields.  There were a few of the children giggling around the baker's hut...pleading for the goodies that had sent their sweetness drifting in the breeze.  Everywhere there was life and joy.  The village seemed renewed again...and thankful.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 306<br> <font color=#993300>(5/1/01 4:33 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/pleiade3/ehipp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring</span><hr size=1> But... in the joy of life... there are trials and honour.  With the spring...came time for the amazons to renew their connection with nature and Artemis.<br>
A quiet began to descend upon the village as eyes turned to see the masked amazon covered in deer hide appear upon the steps of the Queen's hut.  By the mask...all knew it was Hippolyte.  But.. the wiser..and older Amazons also knew.. what spring brought.  The masked Queen walked down the steps...eyes of the tribe..continueing to follow her everymovement.  In her right hand she held a large spear.  The spear was decorated with bones and emblems of Artemis.  Even as Themiscrya was mostly dedicated to Hera, the amazons also knew Artemis kept the life that surrounded the village.  And that life was a gift to the amazons.<br>
Hippolyte stepped up to the small stage/podium in the middle of the village.  There on the podium, she slid the spear into hands of the small 4 foot wooden statue of an ancient amazon standing next to a horse.  It was time...... <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
