<br>
Aly dismounted her horse and took her amazon queen's mask off of her face. Her long blonde hair fell to her shoulders as she looked towards the Queen's hut. She held herself high as she walked towards Hippolyte's hut. The golden belt around her waist kept her body straight and as long as she wore it in any Amazon Lands, no other sister dared to challenge her. She stepped towards the Queen's hut and knocked lightly before entering.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hippolyte?&quot; She asked.<br>
<br>
She looked around the hut slightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Might I ask what is going on? What was that whole thing out there about?&quot; <br>
<br>
Perhaps she has been away from Themiscrya too long. . . ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#993300>(5/7/01 7:01 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/pleiade3/ehipp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring</span><hr size=1> Fingers dipped in the small bowl that held a silvery brown substance.  Then lifted and moved across the top of Hippolyte's chest in a single line.  Brown eyes turned and faced the voice that called her name..then her body following suit.  Before Alysia stood Hippolyte, the northern amazon could see the mark upon the chest.  Hippolyte smiled softly.<br>
<br>
"Yasoo, Alysia," she said calmly.  "I see you have come to see what my message in Scynthia was about."  <br>
Hippolyte moved towards Alysia and gazed into her eyes.  <br>
"Artemis has given us many gifts after the hard winter we were cast with by Zeus.  With this spring... I feel all Amazons should pay homage and respect to her and the creatures she has sent forth into the amazon lands."<br>
