&quot;The hunt might bring her closer to the essence of nature and perhaps she'll make an athelfi or two. Her name is Belle.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 318<br> <font color=#993300>(5/10/01 5:24 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/pleiade3/ehipp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Hunt. . .</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte listened...her brown eyes watching Alysia as she spoke.  Then she smiled, "Yes, do bring your athelfi.  Any amazon who feels she should pay respect to Artemis and the wood should come along.  But, this is not for the weak hearted.  It is a hunt, athelfi."<br>
